iting screen time before bed, keeping rooms cool and dark, and avoiding caffeine after noon.',\n   240→      tags: JSON.stringify(['health', 'science', 'sleep']),\n   241→    },\n   242→    {\n   243→      title: 'Watercolor Painting Basics',\n   244→      body: 'Watercolor painting uses water-soluble pigments on paper. Start with basic techniques: wet-on-wet for soft blends, wet-on-dry for sharp edges, and dry brush for texture. Use quality paper (140lb cold press), a limited palette of primary colors, and practice controlling water ratios.',\n   245→      tags: JSON.stringify(['art', 'painting', 'watercolor']),\n   246→    },\n   247→    {\n   248→      title: 'Blockchain Technology Overview',\n   249→      body: 'Blockchain is a distributed ledger technology where data is stored in linked blocks secured by cryptography. Each block contains a hash of the previous block, creating an immutable chain. Applications extend beyond cryptocurrency to supply chain, healthcare records, and voting systems.',\n   250→      tags: JSON.stringify(['technology', 'blockchain', 'crypto']),\n   251→    },\n   252→    {\n   253→      title: 'Thai Cooking Fundamentals',\n   254→      body: 'Thai cuisine balances sweet, sour, salty, spicy, and bitter flavors. Essential ingredients include fish sauce, lime, lemongrass, galangal, Thai basil, and coconut milk. Master dishes like pad thai, green curry, tom yum soup, and mango sticky rice. Fresh herbs and aromatics are key.',\n   255→      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'thai', 'asian']),\n   256→    },\n   257→    {\n   258→      title: 'Astrophotography Guide',\n   259→      body: 'Capturing the night sky requires a DSLR or mirrorless camera, wide-angle lens, sturdy tripod, and remote shutter release. Use manual mode with wide aperture (f/2.8 or lower), high ISO (1600-6400), and long exposure (15-30 seconds). The 500 rule helps avoid star trails.',\n   260→      tags: JSON.stringify(['photography', 'astronomy', 'techniques']),\n   261→    },\n   262→    {\n   263→      title: 'Functional Programming Concepts',\n   264→      body: 'Functional programming treats computation as evaluation of mathematical functions. Core concepts include pure functions, immutability, higher-order functions, function composition, and avoiding side effects. Languages like Haskell, Elixir, and Clojure embrace FP, while JavaScript and Python support FP patterns.',\n   265→      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'functional', 'concepts']),\n   266→    },\n   267→    {\n   268→      title: 'Home Coffee Roasting',\n   269→      body: 'Roasting coffee at home gives you control over flavor profiles. Green beans progress through drying, first crack, development, and optionally second crack. Light roasts preserve origin flavors, medium roasts balance sweetness and body, dark roasts emphasize roast character. Cool beans quickly after roasting.',\n   270→      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'coffee', 'hobby']),\n   271→    },\n   272→    {\n   273→      title: 'Climbing Mount Kilimanjaro',\n   274→      body: 'Kilimanjaro is the highest peak in Africa at 19,341 feet. The Machame route is the most scenic, taking 6-7 days. Acclimatization is crucial to prevent altitude sickness. No technical climbing skills needed, but physical fitness is essential. The summit offers breathtaking views of the African plains.',\n   275→      tags: JSON.stringify(['travel', 'hiking', 'africa']),\n   276→    },\n   277→    {\n   278→      title: 'CSS Grid Layout Mastery',\n   279→      body: 'CSS Grid provides a two-dimensional layout system for the web. Define rows and columns with grid-template, place items with grid-column and grid-row, and use gap for spacing. Grid areas name regions for intuitive placement. Combine with Flexbox for complete layout control.',\n   280→      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'css', 'web']),\n   281→    },\n   282→    {\n   283→      title: 'Fermentation and Pickling',\n   284→      body: 'Fermentation preserves food using beneficial bacteria. Sauerkraut, kimchi, kombucha, and yogurt are popular fermented foods. Basic lacto-fermentation needs only vegetables, salt, and water. Maintain proper salt ratios (2-3%), keep vegetables submerged, and ferment at room temperature for optimal results.',\n   285→      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'fermentation', 'preservation']),\n   286→    },\n   287→  ];\n   288→}\n   289→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ec0cfedf-b06e-4bd4-8505-f2497aa5a2a1","uuid":"b54c03cb-b2fe-486b-8a88-695e17f8de63","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/src/db.ts","content":"import Database from 'better-sqlite3';\n\nexport function createDatabase(path?: string): Database.Database {\n  const db = path ? new Database(path) : new Database(':memory:');\n\n  db.pragma('journal_mode = WAL');\n  db.pragma('foreign_keys = ON');\n\n  // Create notes table\n  db.exec(`\n    CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS notes (\n      id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,\n      title TEXT NOT NULL,\n      body TEXT NOT NULL,\n      tags TEXT DEFAULT '[]',\n      created_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now')),\n      updated_at TEXT DEFAULT (datetime('now'))\n    )\n  `);\n\n  return db;\n}\n\nexport function seedDatabase(db: Database.Database): void {\n  const insert = db.prepare(`\n    INSERT INTO notes (title, body, tags) VALUES (?, ?, ?)\n  `);\n\n  const notes = getSeedNotes();\n\n  const insertMany = db.transaction((items: { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[]) => {\n    for (const item of items) {\n      insert.run(item.title, item.body, item.tags);\n    }\n  });\n\n  insertMany(notes);\n}\n\nfunction getSeedNotes(): { title: string; body: string; tags: string }[] {\n  return [\n    {\n      title: 'Getting Started with TypeScript',\n      body: 'TypeScript is a typed superset of JavaScript that compiles to plain JavaScript. It adds optional static typing and class-based object-oriented programming to the language. TypeScript is designed for development of large applications and transcompiles to JavaScript.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'typescript', 'javascript']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Introduction to Python Programming',\n      body: 'Python is a high-level, interpreted programming language known for its simplicity and readability. It supports multiple programming paradigms including procedural, object-oriented, and functional programming. Python is widely used in web development, data science, and automation.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['programming', 'python']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Understanding Database Indexing',\n      body: 'Database indexing is a data structure technique used to quickly locate and access data in a database. Indexes are created using columns that are frequently searched against. Without an index, the database must scan every row to find relevant data, which becomes slow for large tables.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['database', 'performance']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Homemade Pasta Recipe',\n      body: 'Making fresh pasta at home is surprisingly simple. You need flour, eggs, salt, and olive oil. Mix the ingredients to form a dough, knead for 10 minutes until smooth, rest for 30 minutes, then roll out and cut into your desired shape. Cook in boiling salted water for 2-3 minutes.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'recipes', 'italian']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Classic Chocolate Chip Cookies',\n      body: 'The perfect chocolate chip cookie requires butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, flour, baking soda, salt, and chocolate chips. Cream the butter and sugars, add eggs and vanilla, mix in dry ingredients, fold in chocolate chips, and bake at 375°F for 9-11 minutes.',\n      tags: JSON.stringify(['cooking', 'recipes', 'baking']),\n    },\n    {\n      title: 'Travel Guide: Tokyo Japan',\n      body: 'Tokyo is a fascinating blend of ultramodern and traditional. Visit the ancient Senso-ji temple, explore